column1: # Each line consists of five elements
# 	- submit_interval	: job generation simulation clock (e.g. 100 means this job will be generated after 100 sim clock from previous one)
# 	- job_duration		: this is standard job duration - this value will be recalcuated based on each VM's cpu performance
# 	- job_deadline		: this is deadline for the job
# 	- input_file		: input file for job. this has prefix such as None
# 						  IC means input file from inside clouds
# 						  OC means input file from outside of clouds.

column2: this also has prefix such as None

column1: # 						  IC means output file will be transfered to storage space inside the cloud (this causes addition storage cost)
# 						  OC means output file will be trasnfered to storage space outside of the cloud
